    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-05-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="304" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d304">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Young</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 12,
                                1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 107.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge receipt of Mr.
                            Pringle’s No. 88, of the 24th ultimo, in relation to the autograph
                            letter from the Provisional President of Honduras to the President of
                            the United States, which was transmitted with his No. 85, of the 10th
                            ultimo.</p>
                <p>Mr. Pringle did right to forward a communication so received from the <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> head of the Government with which
                            intercourse is held.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
